						<tr>
							<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I've recently upgraded a couple of different combat arts and I was alarmed to see that nothing changed except the con color of the icon.  If this has been discussed in another topic I appologize, but I haven't found another topic regarding this issue.
<br />

<br />
I sold a bunch of stuff in vendor mode lately and I had an abundance of gold for the first time in my scouting career.  I decided to upgrade some combat arts so I figured investing in an art that never gets "overwritten" by a later art would be prudent.  I chose to upgrade the Scout combat art, Evade.  I found an Adept III scroll from a vendor and reluctantly parted with 18g for the upgrade.  
<br />

<br />
Before I scribed my new upgrade, I checked the description of Evade at App III level and it read, "Decrease threat by 18-30".  After scribing the Adept III scroll, the icon for Evade turned from a depressing gray to an encouraging white, but I found that the description for Evade STILL read, "Decrease threat by 18-30".  I think this is correct as the art seems to be as ineffective as it was previously.
<br />

<br />
Just today I again upgraded another combat art, Natural Instinct from Apprentice II to Adept I.  The description for App II read briefly, Reconnaissance 10, Ranged 4, and Stalking 10 and after the upgrade to Adept I the description STILL read, Reconnaissance 10, Ranged 4, and Stalking 10.
<br />

<br />
I don't read the Sony forums as I can't get to them from work and when at home I frequent the Web rarely, so I don't know if this is a known issue or not.
<br />

<br />
Dwarrow Nightgaunt
<br />
~35 ranger, Antonia Bayle</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
