							<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">It's true, certain combat arts are worthless to upgrade - though some of them are well worth it. For example, our 20s self buff skill, Bleeder's Talent at the app I level gave +16 AGI and 38% (or 39, can't remember) self haste when cast on yourself. I found a copy of adept I for 1 gold, and it upped the stats to +24 AGI 42% haste. This is WELL worth it IMHO. I've noticed upgrading things like Deadly Strike / Head Shot from App I to Adept I usually add about 30 - 60 damage on to the max, not a lot, but it still helps. 
<br />

<br />
I've personally decided not to upgrade anything past adept I (except Blade Flurry, which I made adept III and was VERY disappointed in the change from app IV) until I start to get my level 38+ skills that will not be upgraded until levels are raised in the future. I'm going to sell the jasper and Indigo ink I have sitting in my inventory that I'd held onto for self upgrade and just save up instead of getting bent over like a few of my friends have in their adept I - adept III upgrades.<br />_________________<br />&#9827; &#9827; :: TUNG FU :: &#9827; &#9827;
<br />

